^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, a few things to talk about. First, of all should Roberta transfer, and how do 4 suit transfers work. In general, if you have a weak hand with a long suit opposite a strong hand, it is more desirable to play in the weak hand's suit because in that suit, the long cards will take tricks, whereas in another suit it may not be possible to score the low cards in the weak hand's long suit. So, Roberta's instinct was correct. |
PG| ***** 75 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The only tradeoff is you have to play at the 3 level, which is kind of high. But with 7 clubs and such a bad hand, I think Roberta made a good decision.|
