NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, how do 4 suit transfers work. Notice that Patti has 2 bids over 2S, either 2N or 3C. Most people play that if Patti bids 2N over 2S, that shows 3 clubs to an honor, whereas if she bids 3 clubs, that denies good club support. That is known as a transfer with "preaccept"  because Patti has 2 bids available she can differentiate between good and bad support, unlike with a major suit transfer. |
PG| ***** 78 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|And if you play 4 suit transfers then 2N is a transfer to diamonds which is a problem because a lot of people forget that. So, if you play 4 suit transfers, make sure you have a smart partner who does not forget. And, btw, to make an invitational raise to 2N (since a direct 2N is a diamond transfer), you bid stayman first and then 2N. Therefore, if responder bids stayman, on rare occasions she will not have  a 4 card major.|
PG| ***** 79 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Some people play a different sort of minor suit transfer. They play 2S is an automatic transfer to 3C, and then responder passes with clubs or corrects to 3D. That is easier to play, but not quite as flexible. I recommend you start with the simpler transfers, as the 2N to diamonds can get you in trouble, and then progress to the more complicated version. Now to the lead directing double by Dee. Normally I am very much in favor of lead directing doubles. However, not sure with AQx it is a good idea. I would like longer spades, and possibly stronger. but I liked the thought. |
